      • createAccount

        @Headers(value="Content-Type:application/json")
 @POST(value="v3/accounts")
retrofit2.Call<AccountInfo> createAccount(@Body
                                                                                                                        AccountCreationReq body,
                                                                                                                        @Query(value="action")
                                                                                                                        java.lang.String action)
        Create a new account. Create a new account. **Example:** ``` curl -X POST https://api.us-east-1.mbedcloud.com/v3/accounts \\ -H 'Authorization: Bearer <api_key>' \\ -H 'content-type: application/json' \\ -d '{\"display_name\": \"MyAccount1\", \"admin_name\": \"accountAdmin1\", \"email\": \"example_admin@myaccount.info\", \"country\": \"United Kingdom\", \"end_market\": \"Smart City\", \"address_line1\": \"110 Fulbourn Rd\", \"city\": \"Cambridge\", \"contact\": \"J. Doe\", \"company\": \"Arm\"}' ```
        Parameters:
        body - Details of the account to create. (required)
        action - Action, either `create` or `enroll`. <ul> <li>`create` creates the account where its admin user has ACTIVE status if `admin_password` was defined in the request, or RESET status if no `admin_password` was defined. If the user already exists, its status is not modified. </li> <li>`enroll` creates the account where its admin user has ENROLLING status. If the user already exists, its status is not modified. Email to finish enrollment or notify the existing user about the new account is sent to the `admin_email` defined in the request. </li></ul> (optional, default to create)
        Returns:
        Call<AccountInfo>

      • getAllAccounts

        @GET(value="v3/accounts")
retrofit2.Call<AccountInfoList> getAllAccounts(@Query(value="status__eq")
                                                                          java.lang.String statusEq,
                                                                          @Query(value="status__in")
                                                                          java.lang.String statusIn,
                                                                          @Query(value="status__nin")
                                                                          java.lang.String statusNin,
                                                                          @Query(value="tier__eq")
                                                                          java.lang.String tierEq,
                                                                          @Query(value="parent__eq")
                                                                          java.lang.String parentEq,
                                                                          @Query(value="end_market__eq")
                                                                          java.lang.String endMarketEq,
                                                                          @Query(value="country__like")
                                                                          java.lang.String countryLike,
                                                                          @Query(value="limit")
                                                                          java.lang.Integer limit,
                                                                          @Query(value="after")
                                                                          java.lang.String after,
                                                                          @Query(value="order")
                                                                          java.lang.String order,
                                                                          @Query(value="include")
                                                                          java.lang.String include,
                                                                          @Query(value="format")
                                                                          java.lang.String format,
                                                                          @Query(value="properties")
                                                                          java.lang.String properties)
        Get all accounts. Returns an array of account objects, optionally filtered by status and tier level. **Example:** ``` curl -X GET https://api.us-east-1.mbedcloud.com/v3/accounts \\ -H 'Authorization: Bearer <api_key>' ```
        Parameters:
        statusEq - An optional filter for account status, ENROLLING, ACTIVE, RESTRICTED, or SUSPENDED. (optional)
        statusIn - An optional filter to retrieve accounts with a specified set of statuses. (optional)
        statusNin - An optional filter to exclude accounts with a specified set of statuses. (optional)
        tierEq - An optional filter for tier level. Must be 0, 1, 2, 98, 99, or omitted. (optional)
        parentEq - An optional filter for parent account ID. (optional)
        endMarketEq - An optional filter for account end market. (optional)
        countryLike - An optional filter for account country. Finds all matches where the filter value is a case-insensitive substring of the result. Example: country__like=LAND matches Ireland. (optional)
        limit - The number of results to return (2-1000). Default 1000. (optional, default to 1000)
        after - The entity ID to fetch after the given one. (optional)
        order - Record order. Acceptable values: ASC, DESC. Default: ASC. (optional, default to ASC)
        include - Comma-separated additional data to return. Currently supported: limits, policies, sub_accounts. (optional)
        format - Format information for the query response. Supported: format=breakdown. (optional)
        properties - Property name returned from account-specific properties. (optional)
        Returns:
        Call<AccountInfoList>
